frameDefinitions: The answer to one open question, the Outcome, is dictated (partially or completely) by the answer to another open question, the Determinant, i.e. if the answer to the Determinant is known, the answer to the Outcome can be predicted.
A Protagonist is sensitive to a Trigger, which has the potential to cause some kind of reaction in the Protagonist.  '' 'Mr. Clinton and his wife Hillary are allergic to cats.'
A Cognizer takes a certain Expectation to be a reliable fact, such that their plans can be based on it.
A concept, Concept_1, is related causally or collocationally to another concept, Concept_2 by means of some evidence.
A Protagonist needs a Means action performed for their Benefit.

An Influencing_entity, an Influencing_situation, or an Influencing_variable has an influence on a Dependent_entity, Dependent_situation,  or a Dependent_variable.  ''  Compare to Subjective_influence.
frameExamples: Economic policy is partially a <t>function</t> of cultural values.
Mr. Clinton and his wife Hillary are <t>allergic</t> to cats.
I can always <t>count</t> <t>on</t> him being late to work when it's raining.
(1) I <t>rely</t> on you to see that my name is not sullied.
More and more doctors realise that diet can <t>influence</t> disease.
listRoleDefinitions: An open question that is (to some degree) predictable from the Determinant.
An open question that determines the <fen>Outcome</fen>.
The <fen>Protagonist</fen> occurs as the External Argument of the targets in this frame. The <fen>Protagonist</fen> represents the one exhibiting the response to the <fen>Trigger</fen>.

The <fen>Trigger</fen> most commonly occurs in a PP Complement headed by <ment>to</ment>. The <fen>Trigger</fen> is that substance or element which causes a health response in the <fen>Protagonist</fen>.
An individual that considers the Expectation certain.
The fact which the <fen>Cognizer</fen> depends on in planning for the future.
The concept which is linked to <fen>Concept_2</fen>.  Generally expressed as the external argument.
The concept which is tied to <fen>Concept_1</fen>.  Generally expressed as a PP complement.
The two concepts expressed jointly.
The person or thing whose needs are served by the <fen>Means</fen> action.
An action or state that the <fen>Means</fen> action brings about and from which the <fen>Protagonist</fen> profits.
The person or thing that performs a <fen>Means</fen> action to the <fen>Benefit</fen> of the <fen>Protagonist</fen>.
An object that the <fen>Protagonist</fen> uses to realize a <fen>Benefit</fen>.
An action or state that the <fen>Protagonist</fen> wants to bring about.  It is more or less the <fen>Benefit</fen> viewed in relation to the <fen>Protagonist</fen> rather than the <fen>Means</fen>.
An action performed either by the <fen>Protagonist</fen> or an <fen>Intermediary</fen> that has a <fen>Benefit</fen> for  the <fen>Protagonist</fen> attached to it.
A thing or person whose behavior has an effect on an <fen>Dependent_entity</fen>, <fen>Dependent_situation</fen>, or <fen>Dependent_variable</fen>.
An entity, usually a thing, that is influenced in its behavior by an <fen>Influencing_entity</fen> or an <fen>Influencing_situation</fen>.
A scalar variable (with unspecified value) which has  an effect on the <fen>Dependent_entity</fen>, <fen>Dependent_situation</fen>, or <fen>Dependent_variable</fen>.
A situation that whose temporal or other characteristics are influenced by an <fen>Influencing_entity</fen>, <fen>Influencing_situation</fen>, or <fen>Influencing_variable</fen>.
A scalar variable, whose value depends on the behavior of an <fen>Influencing_entity</fen>, a <fen>Influencing_situation</fen>, or an <fen>Influencing_variable</fen>.
A situation whose temporal or other characteristics have an effect on a <fen>Dependent_entity</fen>, <fen>Dependent_situation</fen>, or <fen>Dependent_variable</fen>.
The <fen>Degree</fen> to which the <fen>Influencing_entity</fen> effects the <fen>Dependent_entity</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the influence occurs.
The location at which the influencing occurs.
